FORMAT: 1A
HOST: https://csapi.example.com/

# CREATIVE sites API v1.4.4

CREATIVE sites API documentation.

## Authorization

The **authorization header must be present** for all requests. Needed credentials are obtained from our sales representatives.

**Request is authorized only after:**
 - sending auth header with [Basic Auth](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Basic_access_authentication),
 - and sending request from allowed IP address.
 - API only accepts JSON data in requests.
 
## Requests & Responses
### Allowed HTTPS requests
- `POST` - To create resource 
- `PUT` - Update resource
- `GET` - Get a resource or list of resources
- `DELETE` - To delete resource

### Server Responses
- **200** `OK` - the request was successful (some API calls may return 201 instead).
- **201** `Created` - the request was successful and a resource was created.
- **204** `No Content` - the request was successful but there is no representation to return (i.e. the response is empty).
- **400** `Bad Request` - the request could not be understood or was missing required parameters.
- **401** `Unauthorized` - authentication failed or user doesn't have permissions for requested operation.
- **403** `Forbidden` - access denied.
- **404** `Not Found` - resource was not found.
- **405** `Method Not Allowed` - requested method is not supported for resource.
- **426** `Upgrade Required` - method available in higher Plan only, given in the Upgrade header field.
- **429** `Too Many Requests` - too many requests in a given time period (contact sales for your Plan upgrade).

## Changelog

- `2019-05-23` Client activity logs (requests/responses) have been added.
- `2019-07-24` Optional filter parameters for products have been added.
- `2019-09-28` autoAssignParents parameter for products have been added (if set to 'true' the product will be automaticaly assigned to all parent categories of the given category list).
- `2019-10-01` PUT and POST methods for orders have been added.
- `2019-10-24` Optional filter parameters for orders have been added.
- `2019-10-29` Optional filter parameters for customers have been added.
- `2019-11-05` Methods for working with coupons have been added.
- `2019-11-20` Methods for getting activity logs (requests/responses) have been added.
- `2019-11-29` Weight parameter for product variants has been added.
- `2019-12-05` Webhook functionality has been added.
- `2019-12-13` Optional filter parameters foractivity log have been added (filterByPhrase, filterByMethod).
- `2019-12-19` Request queue for POST and PUT methods has been added (Semaphore).
- `2020-02-03` 'availableFrom' option added for product variants (non-standard function, please contact sales).
- `2020-03-13` 'imagesDesc' option added for products.
- `2020-03-17` 'image' option added for categories (in product helper methods).
- `2020-05-15` 'deliveryPointId' parameter added for orders (only for GET methods).
- `2020-12-04` 'virtualVariantName' parameter added for products.
- `2021-02-16` Invoices documentaion extended.
- `2021-03-03` 'creditDiscount' and 'voluntaryContribution' parameter added for orders (only for GET methods).
- `2021-03-17` Customer PUT and POST methods now enable to send encrypted user password.
- `2021-03-19` 'domain' option added for customers.
- `2021-03-19` Method for customer authentication was added.
- `2021-03-25` Sending Social login option added (google, facebook, apple).
- `2021-03-25` Methods for GDPR data proccessing was added.
- `2021-05-18` 'localImagePath' option added for product variants (non-standard function, please contact sales).
- `2021-09-13` 'currency' parameter is now required for updating product prices.
- `2021-10-07` product 'url' for GET Orders has been added.
- `2021-10-11` 'adminNote' option added for orders.
- `2021-10-11` 'invoiceNumber' option added for GET orders.
- `2021-10-11` Information about Currency format, rate and symbols are now available via GET 'currencies' in order helper methods.
- `2022-03-09` 'uom' (Units of measurement) option added for order items.
- `2022-04-07` Added multilang support for products, categories and availabilities.
- `2022-06-23` Added cash rounding support ('cashPaymentRounding' value is automaticaly added to order and 'isCash' parameter is available to set in payment methods).
- `2022-08-25` Added custom store availability for products (non-standard function, please contact sales).
- `2022-10-11` Added custom store availability for (batch) products methods (non-standard function, please contact sales).
- `2022-10-26` GET logs endpoint updated (now runnig thru elastic search).
- `2023-05-25` POST 'ordernotifications' endpoint added for sending mail notifications concerning orders (non-standard function, please contact sales).
- `2023-05-31` Added multilang support for payment and shipping.
- `2023-06-27` Added product Pack (Sets) support.
- `2023-07-12` Added product image metadata - "modified" date (non-standard function, please contact sales).
- `2023-09-06` Optional filter parameters for products have been added.
- `2023-10-31` Optional param 'abortOnError' for BATCH product methods have been added.
- `2023-11-06` Added 'shippingBlacklist' parameter for products methods (non-standard function, please contact sales).
- `2023-12-21` Added additional (read-only) payment data 'transactionDetails' for orders (implemented for GoPay, more will be added in the future).
- `2024-01-31` BATCH order status update method has been added.
- `2024-01-31` Optional param 'abortOnError' for BATCH order status update has been added.
- `2024-06-24` Optional param 'attachDocumentType' for order status update has been added (non-standard function, please contact sales).
- `2024-06-24` Multi document mode added for Invoice management (non-standard function, please contact sales).
- `2024-06-24` Methods for Individual price discounts for specific customers have been added (non-standard function, please contact sales).
- `2024-12-20` Added support for DPD delivery points in Order methods.
- `2025-03-07` Added methods for working with OSS product tax rates (non-standard function, please contact sales).
- `2025-10-09` Added optional param 'taxRate' for Shipping methods allowing to set specific tax rate for shipping (shipping tax rate is also visible in GET orders methods).
- `2026-05-12` Added methods for working with Articles (blog posts) and URL lookup endpoint.

**Last modified:** 2026-05-12 00:00

# Group Product Helpers

Complementary methods for working with propaymentducts (getting information about categories, groups, etc.).

#### Categories [/helper-categories]

Methods for working with categories.

#### Note:
- `parentId` of root categories has to be set to `0`.
- Only categories with no sub-categories can be removed.
- Deleting a category also automatically removes the category relation to products. 

### GET category [GET /categories/{id}]

+ Parameters
    + id: `102109` (number, required) - Category ID

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers
    
            Authorization: Basic QWxhZGRpbjpPcGVuU2VzYW1l
        
+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (Category)
    
### GET categories [GET /categories]

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers
    
            Authorization: Basic QWxhZGRpbjpPcGVuU2VzYW1l
        
+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes 
        + categoryList (array[Category])
    
### PUT category [PUT /categories/{id}]

+ Parameters
    + id: `102109` (number, required) - Category ID

+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes
        + categoryList (array[Category])
         
    + Headers
    
            Authorization: Basic QWxhZGRpbjpPcGVuU2VzYW1l
            
+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Body
    
            {
                "message": "Update successful.",
                "categoryList": [
                    102109
                ]
            }

### POST categories [POST /categories]

+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes
        + categoryList (array[Category])
    + Headers
    
            Authorization: Basic QWxhZGRpbjpPcGVuU2VzYW1l
            
+ Response 201 (application/json)
    + Body
    
            {
                "message": "Import successful.",
                "categoryList": [
                    102109,
                    102110,
                    102111
                ]
            }
            
### DELETE categories [DELETE /categories/{id}]

+ Parameters
    + id: `102109` (number, required) - Category ID

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers
        
            Authorization: Basic QWxhZGRpbjpPcGVuU2VzYW1l
        
+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Body
    
            {
                "message": "Category '102109' was removed."
            }
            
