#### OSS product rates [/helper-ossproductrates]

Methods for setting and getting OSS product tax rates.

#### Note:
-  Usable only when OSS functionality is active (Non-standard function, please contact sales)
- `abortOnError` **param is now available.** Default value is set to *true*. When set to false a partial update is allowed (meaning valid items are processed even if some of the items in batch request are invalid).
- When the `POST` method is used on a product that already has an OSS rate set for the given country the rate will be **updated**.

### GET OSS rate [GET /ossproductrates/{id}]

+ Parameters
    + id: `1234` (number) - Product ID

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers
    
            Authorization: Basic QWxhZGRpbjpPcGVuU2VzYW1l

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes
        + OssProductRateList (array[OssProductRateList])

### GET OSS rates [GET /ossproductrates]

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers
    
            Authorization: Basic QWxhZGRpbjpPcGVuU2VzYW1l

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes
        + OssProductRateList (array[OssProductRateList])
        
        
### POST OSS rates [POST /ossproductrates]

+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes
        + abortOnError: `true` (boolean)
        + userPriceDiscountList (array[OssProductRateList])
    + Headers
        
            Authorization: Basic QWxhZGRpbjpPcGVuU2VzYW1l
        
+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Body
    
            {
                "message": "Update partially failed.",
                "OssProductRateList": [
                    1234,
                    456
                ],
                "errors" : []
            }
    
# Group Order Helpers

Complementary methods for working with orders (getting information about payment methods, order states, etc.).

#### Payment methods [/helper-payments]

Methods for working with order payment methods.

#### Note:
- If `allowedShopperGroup` is set to `0` the payment is visible for every shopper group.

### GET payment method [GET /payments/{id}]

+ Parameters
    + id: `2` (number, required) - Payment method ID
    
+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers
        
            Authorization: Basic QWxhZGRpbjpPcGVuU2VzYW1l
        
+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (Payment)

### GET payment methods [GET /payments]

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers
        
            Authorization: Basic QWxhZGRpbjpPcGVuU2VzYW1l
        
+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes
