# Group Products

Methods for working with products.

## Selecting [/products-select]

Gets product information. Default item cout per page is set to `200` per request.

#### Optional pagination parameters:
- `perPage` - item count per page (maximum allowed value is `1000`) 
- `page` - page number

#### Optional filter parameters:
- `list` - lists / returns only selected values of given records (selecting is allowed only for top level values like `sku`, `stock`, `publish` but not `type` in `parameters`)
- `filterBy` - column name (only top level values like `cdate`, `mdate`, `sku`) 
- `values` - comma separated list of values to be filtered by (%2C encoded comma)
- `from` - available only if 'filterBy' is set to `cdate` or `mdate`
- `to` - available only if 'filterBy' is set to `cdate` or `mdate`

### GET product [GET /products/{id}]

+ Parameters
   + id: `101815` (number, required) - Product ID
   
+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers
    
            Authorization: Basic QWxhZGRpbjpPcGVuU2VzYW1l

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (Product)

### GET products [GET /products{?page,perPage,list,filterBy,values,from,to}]

+ Parameters
   + page: `3` (number, optional) - Page number
   + perPage: `500` (number, optional) - Item count per page
        + Default: `200`
   + list: `sku,stock,publish` (string, optional) - List of values to return separated by comma (%2C encoded comma)
   + filterBy: `sku` (string, optional) - Column name (only top level values like cdate, mdate, sku) 
   + values: `SKU01C,SKU02D` (string, optional) - comma separated list of filtering values (%2C encoded comma)
   + from: `2019-09-20 10:52:11` (string, optional) - Available only if 'filterBy' is set to cdate or mdate
   + to: `2019-09-25 23:15:51` (string, optional) - Available only if 'filterBy' is set to cdate or mdate

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers
    
            Authorization: Basic QWxhZGRpbjpPcGVuU2VzYW1l
   
+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes 
        + metaData (MetaData)
        + productList (array[Product])
        

## Import & Update [/products-import]

The `POST` method creates new product/s and the `PUT` method updates specific product. 

#### Note:
- `PUT (batch) product stocks & availabilities` method is aimed for batch/mass stock updating. Using this method over `PUT product` for stock and availability update is **strongly advised.**
- `PUT (batch) product prices` method is aimed for batch/mass price updating similarly to batch stocks update.
- `abortOnError` param is now available for **batch** methods. Default value is set to `true`. When set to `false` a partial update is allowed (meaning valid items are processed even if some of the items in batch request are invalid). 
- `stock_type1` and `stock_type2` are dynamically generated from `GET stocktypes`
- **WARNING:** `taxRate` moved from `priceList` array to root product structure to reflect shop behavior
- **WARNING:** variant prices have to be entered with or without tax depending on the shop settings (applies for `PUT and POST /products` and `PUT /products/price`) 

### PUT product [PUT /products/{id}]

+ Parameters
    + id: `101815` (number, required) - Product ID

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers
    
            Authorization: Basic QWxhZGRpbjpPcGVuU2VzYW1l
           
    + Attributes
        + productList (array[ProductUpdate])
        
+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Body
    
            "message": "Update successful.",
            "productList": [
                101815
            ]

### PUT (batch) product stocks & availabilities [PUT /products/stock]

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers
    
            Authorization: Basic QWxhZGRpbjpPcGVuU2VzYW1l

    + Attributes
        + abortOnError: `true` (boolean)
        + stockList (array[StockAvail])
        
+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Body
    
            {
                "message": "Update successful."
                "stockList": [
                    101815
                ],
                "errors": []
            }
            
### PUT (batch) product prices [PUT /products/price]

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers
    
            Authorization: Basic QWxhZGRpbjpPcGVuU2VzYW1l

    + Attributes
        + abortOnError: `true` (boolean)
        + priceList (array[BatchPrice])
        
+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Body
    
            {
               "message": "Update successful.",
               "priceList": [
                    101815
                ],
                "errors": []
            }

### POST products [POST /products]

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers
    
            Authorization: Basic QWxhZGRpbjpPcGVuU2VzYW1l
           
    + Attributes
        + productList (array[Product])

+ Response 201 (application/json)
    + Body
    
            {
                "message": "Import successful.",
                "productList": [
                    101815,
                    101816,
                    101817
                ]
            }
            
## Removing [/products-delete]

Removes specific product.

### DELETE product [DELETE /products/{id}]

+ Parameters
    + id: `101815` (number, required) - Product ID

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers
    
            Authorization: Basic QWxhZGRpbjpPcGVuU2VzYW1l
            
+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Body
    
