                "message": "Product '101815' was removed."
            }

# Group Orders

Methods for working with orders.

## Selecting [/order-select]

Gets order information. Default item cout per page is set to `200` per request.

#### Optional pagination parameters:
- `perPage` - item count per page (maximum allowed value is `1000`) 
- `page` - page number

#### Optional filter parameters:
- `filterBy` - column name (only top level values like `cdate`, `mdate`, `orderStatus`) 
- `values` - comma separated list of values to be filtered by (%2C encoded comma)
- `from` - available only if 'filterBy' is set to `cdate` or `mdate`
- `to` - available only if 'filterBy' is set to `cdate` or `mdate`
- `addOrderHistory` - adds order status history to result
- `addTrackingUrl` - adds tracking url to result (if exists and APP 160 is activated)
- `domain` - filters orders by domain of origin

### GET order [GET /orders/{id}]

+ Parameters
    + id: `101815` (number, required) - Order ID
    
+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers
    
            Authorization: Basic QWxhZGRpbjpPcGVuU2VzYW1l
            
+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (Order)

### GET orders [GET /orders{?page,perPage,filterBy,values,from,to,domain}]

+ Parameters
   + page: `3` (number, optional) - Page number
   + perPage: `500` (number, optional) - Item count per page
        + Default: `200`
    + filterBy: `orderStatus` (string, optional) - Column name (only top level values like cdate, mdate, orderStatus) 
    + values: `S,D,C` (string, optional) - comma separated list of filtering values (%2C encoded comma)
    + from: `2019-09-20 10:52:11` (string, optional) - Available only if 'filterBy' is set to cdate or mdate
    + to: `2019-09-25 23:15:51` (string, optional) - Available only if 'filterBy' is set to cdate or mdate
    + addOrderHistory: true (boolean, optional) - Adds order status history to result
    + addTrackingUrl: true (boolean, optional) - Adds tracking url to result (if exists and APP 160 is activated)
    + domain: `www.domain.com` (string, optional) - Filters orders by domain of origin

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers
    
            Authorization: Basic QWxhZGRpbjpPcGVuU2VzYW1l
            
+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes 
        + metaData (MetaData)
        + orderList (array[Order])

## Import & Update [/order-import]

The `POST` method creates new order/s and the `PUT` method updates specific order.

#### Note:
- A valid `phone` number must contain **16 characters or less** (allowed characters are: **'0-9, +, [space], /, -, –'** of which these three: **'/, -, –'** will be converted to [space])
- Please mind that the data structures and required fields for `PUT` and `POST orders` metod are **different**.
- With `POST orders` the shipping address is only updated when the address `id` is given, when the address `id` is missing or not existing a new shipping address will be created. 
- `abortOnError` param is now available for **batch** order status update method. Default value is set to `true`. When set to `false` a partial update is allowed (meaning valid items are processed even if some of the items in batch request are invalid). 
- The domain of the order changes based on the currency (prices must be in the provided currency).
    - supported currencies: `CZK, HUF, PLN, BGN, RON, UAH`

### PUT order [PUT /orders/{id}]

+ Parameters
    + id: `101815` (number, required) - Order ID
    
+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes
        + orderList (array[OrderUpdate])
    + Headers
    
            Authorization: Basic QWxhZGRpbjpPcGVuU2VzYW1l
   
+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Body
    
            {
                "orderList": 101815
            }
                     
### PUT order status [PUT /orders/status/{id}]

+ Parameters
    + id: `101815` (number, required) - Order ID
    
+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes
        + orderList: (OrderStatusOnOrder)

    + Headers
    
            Authorization: Basic QWxhZGRpbjpPcGVuU2VzYW1l
   
+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Body
    
            {
                "message": "Update successful.", 
                "orderList": [
                101815
                ]
            }
            
### PUT (batch) order statuses [PUT /orders/status]

+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes
        + abortOnError: `true` (boolean)
        + orderList: (array[OrderStatusOnOrder]) 

    + Headers
    
            Authorization: Basic QWxhZGRpbjpPcGVuU2VzYW1l
   
+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Body
    
            {
                "message": "Update successful.", 
                "orderList": [
                101815
                ]
            }

### POST orders [POST /orders]

+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes
        + orderList (array[OrderCreate])
    + Headers
    
            Authorization: Basic QWxhZGRpbjpPcGVuU2VzYW1l
   
+ Response 201 (application/json)
    + Body
    
            {
                "orderList": [
                    101815,
                    101816
                ]
            }

## Removing [/order-delete]

Removes specific order.

#### Note:
- after the order is removed the stock level of ordered items is updated to the state before the order was placed.

### DELETE order [DELETE /orders/{id}]

