                "message": "Order '101815' was removed."
            }


# Group Invoices

There are **three sets of methods** for working with invoices. 

#### Note:
- The **first "basic mode"** is active by default and is used only for getting basic information such as if the invoce exists, when it was created and other. *Only `GET` method is allowed*.
- The **second "single doc. mode"** is actived upon contacting our sales department. This set of methods allows uploading own invoices in PDF format. *All methods are allowed (`GET`, `PUT`, `POST`, `DELETE`)*.
- The **third "multi doc. mode"** is actived upon contacting our sales department. This set of methods allows uploading mulitple documents per order (invoices, creditnotes, proforma and etc.) in PDF format. *All methods are allowed (`GET`, `PUT`, `POST`, `DELETE`)*.
- Document types and other settings for `multi doc. mode` can be set by using the **Order multi doc. invoice settings** methods in **Order Heplers** section

## Selecting "basic mode" [/invoices-select]

### GET invoice [GET /invoices/{id}]

+ Parameters
    + id: `2` (number, required) - Order ID
    
+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers
    
            Authorization: Basic QWxhZGRpbjpPcGVuU2VzYW1l

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (InvoiceBasic)

