# Group Customers
Methods for working with customers.

## Selecting [/users-select]

#### Optional pagination parameters:
- `perPage` - item count per page (maximum allowed value is `1000`) 
- `page` - page number

#### Optional filter parameters:
- `filterBy` - column name (only top level values like `cdate`, `mdate`, `orderStatus`) 
- `values` - comma separated list of values to be filtered by (%2C encoded comma)
- `from` - available only if 'filterBy' is set to `cdate` or `mdate`
- `to` - available only if 'filterBy' is set to `cdate` or `mdate`

#### Note:
- `priceDiscount` is available only fo `GET` methods (non-standard function, please contact sales)

### GET customer [GET /users/{id}]

+ Parameters
   + id: `236` (number, required) - Customer ID
   
+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers
    
            Authorization: Basic QWxhZGRpbjpPcGVuU2VzYW1l

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (Customer)

### GET customers [GET /users{?page,perPage,filterBy,values,from,to}]

+ Parameters
   + page: `3` (number, optional) - Page number
   + perPage: `500` (number, optional) - Item count per page
        + Default: `200`
    + filterBy: `orderStatus` (string, optional) - Column name (only top level values like cdate, mdate, orderStatus) 
    + values: `S,D,C` (string, optional) - comma separated list of filtering values (%2C encoded comma)
    + from: `2019-09-20 10:52:11` (string, optional) - Available only if 'filterBy' is set to cdate or mdate
    + to: `2019-09-25 23:15:51` (string, optional) - Available only if 'filterBy' is set to cdate or mdate

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers
    
            Authorization: Basic QWxhZGRpbjpPcGVuU2VzYW1l

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes
        + metaData (MetaData)
        + customerList (array[Customer])
        
## Authentication [/users-auth]

Checks the correctness of given customer credentials (please contact sales). Currently there are **two method** to check customer authentication:
- with **standard credentials** sending email and password
- with **social login** sending hybrid auth identifier and provider

#### Note:
- When sending customer `password` following criteria **must** be met:
    - OpenSSL **cipher method** must be choosen / configured (please contact sales)
    - OpenSSL **secret passphrase** must be choosen / configured (please contact sales)
    - `initializationVector` parameter is required when sending encrypted password
    - both `password` and `initializationVector` have to be Base64 encoded

### POST customer authentication [POST /users/auth]

+ Request Standard credentials (application/json)
    + Attributes (CustomerAuthNormal)
    + Headers
    
            Authorization: Basic QWxhZGRpbjpPcGVuU2VzYW1l
            
+ Request Social login (application/json)
    + Attributes (CustomerAuthHybrid)
    + Headers
    
            Authorization: Basic QWxhZGRpbjpPcGVuU2VzYW1l
            
+ Response 200 (application/json)
     + Body
    
            {
                "message": "Customer was successfully authenticated.",
                "auth": {
                    "email": "john.smith@gmail.com",
                    "id": 456
                }
            }
            
+ Response 401 (application/json)
     + Body
    
            {
                "message": "Customer authentication failed, wrong credentials."
            }

## Import & Update [/users-import]

#### Note:
- When using `POST customers` the **shipping** address `id` is not required
- When using `PUT customers` the **shipping** address `id` is required for updating existing address, if `id` is not provided another address will be added automatically (with a newly generated id)
- A valid `phone` number must contain **16 characters or less** (allowed characters are: **'0-9, +, [space], /, -, –'** of which these three: **'/, -, –'** will be converted to [space])
- When sending customer `password` following criteria **must** be met:
    - OpenSSL **cipher method** must be choosen / configured (please contact sales)
    - OpenSSL **secret passphrase** must be choosen / configured (please contact sales)
    - `initializationVector` parameter is required when sending encrypted password
    - both `password` and `initializationVector` have to be Base64 encoded
- When sending **social login information** following criteria **must** be met:
    - `hybridAuthIdentifier` parameter is required (please contact sales)
    - `provider` parameter is required (please contact sales)
    - `domain` parameter is required

### PUT customer [PUT /users/{id}]

+ Parameters
    + id: `236` (number, required) - Customer ID
    
+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes
        + customerList (array[CustomerNoGdpr])
    + Headers
    
            Authorization: Basic QWxhZGRpbjpPcGVuU2VzYW1l

+ Response 200 (application/json)
     + Body
    
            {
                "message": "Update succesful.",
                "customerList": [
                    236
                ]
            }

### POST customers [POST /users]

+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes
        + customerList (array[CustomerNoGdpr])
    + Headers
    
            Authorization: Basic QWxhZGRpbjpPcGVuU2VzYW1l
            
+ Response 201 (application/json)
    + Body
    
            {
                "message": "Import succesful.",
                "customerList": [
                    236,
                    237
                ]
            }

