# Group Articles

Methods for working with articles (blog posts).

## Selecting [/articles-select]

Gets article information. Default item count per page is set to `200` per request.

#### Optional pagination parameters:
- `perPage` - item count per page (maximum allowed value is `1000`)
- `page` - page number

#### Optional filter parameters:
- `filterBy` - column name to filter by (only top level values like `cdate`, `mdate`, `title`)
- `values` - comma separated list of values to filter by (%2C encoded comma)
- `from` - available only if `filterBy` is set to `cdate` or `mdate`
- `to` - available only if `filterBy` is set to `cdate` or `mdate`

### GET article [GET /articles/{id}]

+ Parameters
    + id: `192` (number, required) - Article ID

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers

            Authorization: Basic QWxhZGRpbjpPcGVuU2VzYW1l

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes
        + articleList (array[Article])

### GET articles [GET /articles{?page,perPage,filterBy,values,from,to}]

+ Parameters
    + page: `1` (number, optional) - Page number
    + perPage: `200` (number, optional) - Item count per page
        + Default: `200`
    + filterBy: `cdate` (string, optional) - Column name to filter by (only top level values like `cdate`, `mdate`, `title`)
    + values: `2024-01-01,2024-06-01` (string, optional) - Comma separated list of filtering values (%2C encoded comma)
    + from: `2024-01-01 00:00:00` (string, optional) - Available only if `filterBy` is set to `cdate` or `mdate`
    + to: `2024-12-31 23:59:59` (string, optional) - Available only if `filterBy` is set to `cdate` or `mdate`

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers

            Authorization: Basic QWxhZGRpbjpPcGVuU2VzYW1l

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes
        + metaData (ArticleMetaData)
        + articleList (array[Article])

## Import & Update [/articles-import]

The `POST` method creates new article/s and the `PUT` method updates a specific article.

#### Note:
- `title` and `authorId` are required for POST (import).
- `sef` is auto-generated from `title` if not provided on import.
- `visibleFrom` and `visibleTo` accept date-time string or `null`.
- `hiddenOnDomains` accepts a list of domain hostnames configured in the shop.
- `access` accepts one of: `public`, `registered`, `administrator`.
- `mainImage` accepts a URL — the image will be downloaded and stored by the server.
- `translations` keys are language ISO codes (e.g. `sk`, `cz`).

### PUT article [PUT /articles/{id}]

+ Parameters
    + id: `192` (number, required) - Article ID

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers

            Authorization: Basic QWxhZGRpbjpPcGVuU2VzYW1l

    + Attributes
        + articleList (array[ArticleUpdate])

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Body

            {
                "message": "Update successful.",
                "articleList": [
                    192
                ]
            }

### POST articles [POST /articles]

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers

            Authorization: Basic QWxhZGRpbjpPcGVuU2VzYW1l

    + Attributes
        + articleList (array[ArticleImport])

+ Response 201 (application/json)
    + Body

            {
                "message": "Import successful.",
                "articleList": [
                    192,
                    193
                ]
            }

### DELETE article [DELETE /articles/{id}]

+ Parameters
    + id: `192` (number, required) - Article ID

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers

            Authorization: Basic QWxhZGRpbjpPcGVuU2VzYW1l

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Body

            {
                "message": "Article '192' was removed."
            }

# Group URLs

Methods for getting SEF URLs for products, categories and articles. Useful for resolving canonical URLs or building sitemaps. All translations across configured languages are always returned.

#### Supported entity types:
- `product` - e-shop product
- `category` - e-shop category
- `article` - blog article

#### Optional pagination parameters:
- `perPage` - item count per page (maximum allowed value is `1000`)
- `page` - page number

## URL lookup [/urls-info]

### GET URL [GET /urls/{entityType}/{id}]

+ Parameters
    + entityType (enum[string], required) - Entity type
        + `product` - E-shop product
        + `category` - E-shop category
        + `article` - Blog article
    + id: `101815` (number, required) - Entity ID

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers

            Authorization: Basic QWxhZGRpbjpPcGVuU2VzYW1l

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Body

            {
                "metaData": [],
                "urlList": [
                    {
                        "id": 101815,
                        "url": "https://www.example.com/fancy-sport-t-shirt",
                        "translations": {
                            "cz": "https://cz.example.com/fancy-sport-t-shirt"
                        }
                    }
                ]
            }

### GET URLs [GET /urls/{entityType}{?page,perPage}]

+ Parameters
    + entityType (enum[string], required) - Entity type
        + `product` - E-shop product
        + `category` - E-shop category
        + `article` - Blog article
    + page: `1` (number, optional) - Page number
    + perPage: `200` (number, optional) - Item count per page
        + Default: `200`

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers

            Authorization: Basic QWxhZGRpbjpPcGVuU2VzYW1l

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Body

            {
                "metaData": {
                    "page": 1,
                    "perPage": 200,
                    "total": 312,
                    "pages": 2
                },
                "urlList": [
                    {
                        "id": 101815,
                        "url": "https://www.example.com/fancy-sport-t-shirt",
                        "translations": {
                            "cz": "https://cz.example.com/fancy-sport-t-shirt"
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        "id": 192,
                        "url": "https://www.example.com/blog/my-article",
                        "translations": {
                            "cz": "https://cz.example.com/blog/muj-clanek"
                        }
                    }
                ]
            }

# Group Error handling

Methods for better understanding of error handling.

## Basic information [/error-info]

### GET error code description [GET /errorcodes/{id}]

+ Parameters
    + id: `1001` (number, required) - Error code

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Body
    
            {
                "errorCodes": {
                    "1001": "Product with given sku already exists."
                }
            }

### GET error code descriptions [GET /errorcodes]

+ Response 200 (application/json)
     + Attributes
        + errorCodes (ErrorCodes)
        
        
# Group Logs

Methods for getting information about requests done in the past. 

#### Note:
- logged data from `GET` requests is truncated (as it is not so important) to minimize the log size.

## Obtaining activity logs [/logs-info]

#### Optional filter parameters:
- `filterByPhrase` - search by phrase (case insensitive, both request and response content is searched) 
- `filterByMethod` - search by method (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)
- both filter parameters can be used concurrently.

### GET log [GET /logs/{date}{?filterByPhrase,filterByMethod}]

Gets information about all requests from the given `date`.

+ Parameters
    + date: `2019-11-18` (string, required) - Log date
    + filterByPhrase: `T-shirt` (string, optional) - search by phrase (case insensitive, both request and response content is searched)
    + filterByMethod: `PUT` (string, optional) - search by method (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE) 
    

+ Response 200 (application/json)
     + Attributes
        + logs (Log)


## Data Structures
## Product
+ id: `101815` (number) - Product ID
+ sku: `IOF21346` (string, required) - Product Code (SKU)
+ ean: `8596164008607` (string) - Ean code
+ name: `Fancy sport T-shirt` (string) - Product name
+ sef: `fancy-sport-t-shirt` (string) - Product sef name
+ description: `Great for all kind of things` (string) - Product description
+ shortDescription: `Great T-shirt` (string) - Product short description
+ mainImage: `https://www.example.com/path/to/image/image01.jpg` (string) - Main image URL
+ imageList: (array) - List o secondary images
    + `https://www.example.com/path/to/image/image02.jpg` (string) - Image URL
+ imagesDesc: `Fancy sport T-shirt image description` (string) - Description of secondary images (Alt text) 
+ publish: `true` (boolean) - Product visibility
+ unsaleable: `false` (boolean) - Product is unsaleable
+ permanentlyUnavailable: `false` (boolean) - Product is permanently unavailable
+ availability: `108` (number) - Availability ID
+ availableFrom: `2017-07-26` (string) - Date when the product will be available
+ specialGroupList: (array) - List of product special groups 
    + `17` (number) - Special group ID
    + `2` (number) - Special group ID
+ cdate: `2017-07-20 16:20:34` (string) - Product creation date
+ mdate: `2019-05-02 09:25:43` (string) - Product modification date
+ manufacturer: `302` (number) - Manufacturer ID
+ primaryCategory: `102426` (number) - Primary category ID
+ categories: (array) - List of product categories
    + `102426` (number) - Product category ID
    + `102427` (number) - Product category ID
+ autoAssignParents: `false` (boolean) - If set to 'true' the product will be automaticaly assigned to all parent categories of the given category list
+ stock: `39` (number) - Product quantity (on stock)
+ supplierStock: `15` (number) - Product supplier quantity (on supplier stock)
+ stock_type1: `12` (number) - Product stock type quantity (dynamic stock types are obtained via GET /stocktypes)
+ stock_type2: `12` (number) - Product stock type quantity (dynamic stock types are obtained via GET /stocktypes)
+ weight: `2.5` (number) - Product weight
+ weightUnit: `kg` (string) - Product weight unit (kg, pounds)
+ uomId: `2` (number) - Unit of measurement ID
+ taxRate: `20` (number) - Product Tax Rate
+ virtualVariantId: `sport-shirts-spring-19`  (string) - Virtual variant identifier
+ virtualVariantName: `red`  (string) - Virtual variant name
+ activeVariants: (array) - Code List of product variants
    + `product-code-variant-1` (string) - Variant code
+ variants: (array[Variant]) - List of product variants
+ parameters:  (array[Parameter]) - List of product parameters
+ priceList:  (array[Price]) - List of product prices
+ metaTitle: `Great T-shirt` (string) - Product meta title (optional, if no value is provided a system generated value is used instead)
+ metaDesc: `Great for all kind of things` (string) - Product meta description (optional, if no value is provided a system generated value is used instead)
+ metaKeywords: `shirt, sport, fasion` (string) - Product meta keywords
+ translations: (object) - Product translations
    + cz: (object)
        + name: (string) - Product name translation
        + sef: (string) - Product sef translation
        + shortDescription: (string) - Product short description translation
        + description: (string) - Product description translation
        + metaTitle: (string) - Product meta title translation
        + metaDesc: (string) - Product meta description translation
        + metaKeywords: (string) - Product meta keywords translation
+ store: (array[ProductStore]) - List of product stores (non-standard function)
+ set: (array[Set]) - List of set items (non-standard function for variants)
+ imageMetaData: (object) - Image Meta Data  (non-standard function)
    + mainImage: (object)
        + url: `https://www.example.com/path/to/image/image01.jpg` (string) - Main image URL
        + mdate: `2023-07-11 23:15:51` (string) - Image modification date
    + imageList: (array) - Array of secondary images meta data
        + (object)
            + url: `https://www.example.com/path/to/image/image02.jpg` (string) - Secondary image URL
            + mdate: `2023-07-11 23:15:51` (string) - Image modification date
+ shippingBlacklist: (array) - List of blacklisted shipping rates (non-standard function)
    + `27` (number) - Shipping rate ID
    + `266` (number) - Shipping rate ID

